## Why This Is Asked

Tests understanding of end-to-end AWS data pipelines using AI services, speaker diarization, secure data handling, error management, IAM least-privilege principles, and cost optimization for beginner-level implementations.

## Key Concepts

- Event-driven architecture: S3 → Lambda → Amazon Transcribe → DynamoDB
- Transcribe diarization for per-speaker transcript segmentation
- Multi-format output storage (full + individual speaker transcripts)
- DynamoDB indexing strategy with composite keys
- IAM security with least-privilege access patterns
- Error handling with retries and dead-letter queues
- Data privacy through KMS encryption and access controls
- Cost monitoring and optimization for short audio clips

## Code Example

```javascript
// Example Lambda: S3 event handling to start Transcribe
exports.handler = async (event) => {
  const record = event.Records[0];
  const bucket = record.s3.bucket.name;
  const key = record.s3.object.key;

  // Start Transcribe job with diarization
  const transcribeParams = {
    TranscriptionJobName: `interview-${Date.now()}`,
    LanguageCode: 'en-US',
    MediaFormat: key.split('.').pop(),
    Media: { MediaFileUri: `s3://${bucket}/${key}` },
    Settings: {
      ShowSpeakerLabels: true,
      MaxSpeakerLabels: 10
    },
    OutputBucketName: process.env.OUTPUT_BUCKET
  };

  await transcribe.startTranscriptionJob(transcribeParams).promise();
};
```

